  <excursions><![CDATA[<p><strong>Pre-bookable Excursions</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Bear Watching Experience</strong> £40</li>
</ul>
<p>Depart by coach from your hotel mid-afternoon to the 'Devil's Pass'<br />followed by an easy/moderate walk to the Cece Refuge with fabulous<br />views over the Abruzzo mountain range. Time to explore the area and<br />enjoy a typical Abruzzo mountain meal with drinks included followed<br />by ‘The Bear Watch’. Return to Pescasseroli around 10-10.30pm.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Camosciara Waterfalls and Lake Barrea</strong> £30</li>
</ul>
<p>Leave after breakfast for the village of Villetta Barrea. You will then<br />undertake a beautiful guided walk through beech tree forests to the<br />Camosciara Waterfalls, admiring the flora and fauna of the area on the<br />way. We continue the walk from the waterfalls to the elevated village<br />of Civitella Alfedena where you can enjoy spectacular views of Lake<br />Barrea. You will also have the opportunity to visit the Wolf Sanctuary.<br />A moderate walk takes us back to Villetta Barrea.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>On the Tracks of Wolf Howling</strong> £22</li>
</ul>
<p>Wolf howling is a technique that was used in the past by wolf hunters in<br />Abruzzo. Today it is used for research purposes. On this dusk walking<br />tour you will experience howling with the wolves and your guide will talk<br />you through the wild nature of this walk under starry skies. The walk is<br />moderate in difficulty and lasts approx. 1½ hrs.</p>
<p><br /><em>Prices shown are for guidance only. Please note we act at all times as selling agent for </em><em>the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions. See</em> <a href="/{localLink:66d6dfd2-b127-48e8-b6d8-228d6e59ea65}" title="Terms &amp; Conditions"><em>terms &amp; conditions.</em></a></p>]]></excursions>
