<h2>Rome City Break</h2>
<p>Rome's turbulent history, its magnificent rise to power, followed by an equally dramatic downfall is the subject of scores of books and films, yet these little prepare you for exploring first hand this grand and vivacious city. Rome is a living and breathing museum where fast paced modern life revolves around a stunning ancient backdrop. Historic sites greet you at every turn; be awed by the Colosseum and Pantheon from Rome's glorious Imperial era and across the Tiber river to the unique Vatican City and Reinassance Rome's beautiful Sistine Chapel. In the summer a season of concerts begins with performances in some of the cities' most beautiful palaces, churches and courtyards, as well as contemporary cultural events - films, music, dance and theatre. Combine old wonders with the delights of Modern Rome; street markets, stylish boutiques, the vibrant café culture - in short, La Dolce Vita!</p>
