  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p>Pescasseroli is the gateway to the beautiful Abruzzo National Park, situated right in the heart of the Apennines. There are fine walking routes to be enjoyed (approx 150 marked) from easy, gentle strolls to more challenging hikes, through medieval mountain top villages, beech forest, meadows and valleys.</p>
<p><strong>Popular Walks Include:</strong> (Available from 21 May until 30 Sep)</p>
<p><strong>Boschi della Difesa / Easy / Monday / 9am-1pm / approx 3½ hrs</strong> An atmospheric walk through Boschi della Difesa, the National Park's most ancient beech woods, typical habitat of the marsican brown bear, red deer and wild boar.</p>
<p><strong>Val Fondillo / Easy/ Friday / 8.10am-1.45pm / approx 4 hrs</strong></p>
<p>A 10 minute bus ride to the mouth of the Val Fondillo, a beautiful valley<br />blessed with a wealth of wildlife. Follow the banks of the Fondillo, a<br />crystal clear stream, as it runs through one of the most beautiful beech<br />forests of the Apennines. Bus costs approx €3.</p>]]></walkingDescription>
